JOHANNESBURG Orlando Pirates are hoping to break a winless streak in 2017 when they play perennial rivals Kaizer Chiefs in an Absa Premiership clash at the FNB Stadium on Saturday afternoon.Pirates have been having a dreadful run of form; the Buccaneers last won a game in November.Chiefs, on the other hand, head into the derby on the back of a seven-game unbeaten run, which included five wins on the trot.The last two league matches between Chiefs and Pirates ended in draws.Tweets about #Sowetoderby AND (FROM:@Orlando_Pirates since:2017-03-04 until:2017-03-05) Tweets about #AbsaPrem AND (@KaizerChiefs since:2017-03-04 until:2017-03-05) eNCA